<item>
            <title>[PIG-2525] Support pluggable PigProgressNotifcationListeners on the command line</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-2525</link>
                <project id="12310730" key="PIG">Pig</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;It would be convenient to be able to implement &lt;tt&gt;PigProcessNotifcationListener&lt;/tt&gt; and to wire it into a pig script. This jira is to support setting a listener and its constructor args on the command, perhaps like this:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;noformat&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
pig -j MyListener -J &quot;foo,bar,bat&quot; -f my_script.pig&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;tt&gt;noformat&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;where &lt;tt&gt;MyListener&lt;/tt&gt; takes a single string in the constructor which will get passed &lt;tt&gt;foo,bar,bat&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
